**My Analysis of the Administrative Unit Changes**

Okay, let's break this down. The user provided an old address: "Xã Phú Hiệp, Huyện Tam Nông, Tỉnh Đồng Tháp" and is asking me to determine the new administrative unit(s) based on available resolutions. First, I parsed the old address. I zeroed in on "Xã Phú Hiệp" as the ward and "Tỉnh Đồng Tháp" as the province, ignoring the district for the purpose of this analysis.

My approach involves systematically checking various resolutions.  I began with the overarching province resolutions to confirm the status of "Tỉnh Đồng Tháp". Resolution 60-NQ/TW confirmed it remains unchanged.

Next, I delved into resolutions potentially affecting the specific ward. I cross-referenced "Xã Phú Hiệp" within "Tỉnh Đồng Tháp" against all available resolutions.  Two resolutions were relevant: 1654/NQ-UBTVQH15 (An Giang) and 1663/NQ-UBTVQH15 (Đồng Tháp). I immediately eliminated the An Giang resolution because it was not within the correct province.

Resolution 1663/NQ-UBTVQH15 (Đồng Tháp) was the key.  Line 9 explicitly states that "Xã Phú Hiệp" merges with "Xã Phú Đức" to form a new ward called "Xã Tam Nông".  I double-checked line 12 but determined that it did not mention "Xã Phú Hiệp." Resolution 1676/NQ-UBTVQH15 (Phú Thọ) was not relevant because it pertained to a different province.

I then consulted the "New wards" data.  The entry: `{"ward_code":"30010","ward_name":"Xã Tam Nông","province_name":"Tỉnh Đồng Tháp"}` perfectly aligns with my findings from resolution 1663/NQ-UBTVQH15.  The new ward is indeed "Xã Tam Nông" within "Tỉnh Đồng Tháp".

I eliminated the other options within the "New wards" data because they either had the wrong name ("Xã Phú Cường" or the wrong province (An Giang/Phú Thọ).

Therefore, my conclusion is definitive. "Xã Phú Hiệp, Tỉnh Đồng Tháp" has been reorganized and is now "Xã Tam Nông, Tỉnh Đồng Tháp", confirming that the high confidence match is warranted. The evidence from the resolutions is direct and unambiguous.
